    <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>

    <p>For personal loans and mortgage loans, Users can opt for fixed or floating rates. Interest payable on floating rate is reset every month and is calculated using bank’s internal External Benchmark rate.</p>

    <p>Current rate of interest under fixed rate option is 16% p.a.</p>

    <p>No security is to be provided for personal loans.</p>

    <p>Default or delay in payments will lead to your Credit Score being affected as per regulatory guidelines. In case of delay or default, a penalty of 1% of outstanding per month is levied over and above applicable interest rate.</p>

    <p>All disputes arising out of this agreement can be sent to the banking ombudsman.</p>

    <p>Cymbal reserves the right to recall the loan by giving 30-days notice to the customer.</p>

    <p>Disbursement will be done only to the account that has been selected for pre-approval.</p>

    <p>Loans cannot be used for trading in capital market, buying shares, bonds, gambling, or illegal activities.</p>

    <p>For Digital Personal Loans, customers need to specify the bank IFSC code and Account Number for disbursement. As per policy, disbursement will only be done in savings accounts held in a single name. Joint accounts not allowed for disbursement.</p>

    <p>All approvals are at the sole discretion of Cymbal Bank.</p>

    <p>Maximum amount available under pre-approved loan and digital personal loan is 10,00,000. For loan against fixed deposit and loan against securities, the maximum loan is 10,000,000 (1 Crore).</p>

    <p>Cymbal Bank reserves the right to change the list of securities or the haircut for overdraft against securities. In case of valuation shortfall, customers will have 24 hours to provide additional securities.</p>

    <p>The bank has absolute discretion to sell or dispose of securities in the event of a margin shortfall not being covered within 24 hours of notice.</p>

    <p>Min. income criteria is Rs 25,000 p.m (pre-tax) for personal loans and two-wheeler loans and Rs. 75,000 for home loans and car loans.</p>

    <p>At present, the interest rate under External Benchmark (EBLR) is being reset by the Bank on 1st of every month per Banks guidelines.</p>

